-value our findings suggest that\nthe obscured fraction depends on quasar luminosity. The space density of\nobscured quasars is ~5x that inferred for UV-bright quasars from the SDSS\nluminosity function at Mi<-30 but seems to drop at lower luminosities even\naccounting for various sources of incompleteness in our sample (abridged).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 25 Mar 2012 18:45:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 26 Jul 2012 10:01:47 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 11 Sep 2012 09:15:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
